<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Aniwye
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.beesum-communications.com/nation/archive/volume_13/13-04/kuik_legend.html
">Kuikuhâchâu and Wâniyûyâu</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.ourvoices.ca/index/ourvoices-story-action/id.0136
">Legend of the Giant Skunk</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Two Cree legends about Wolverine slaying Giant Skunk (Aniwye.)
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Related Native American Legends</a>
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B008GOKLU6/natilangofthe-20
">Myths and Folk-lore of the Timiskaming Algonquin and Timagami Ojibwa</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Classic collection of Algonquin legends including the story of Aniwye and Fisher.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0873514041/natilangofthe-20
">Living Our Language</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe legends and oral histories.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0816673829/natilangofthe-20
">The Mishomis Book: Voice of the Ojibway</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Excellent book by a Native author exploring Ojibway legends and traditions.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0803293380/natilangofthe-20
">Algonquian Spirit</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Rich anthology of stories, songs, and oral history from the Ojibway and other Algonquian tribes.  
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of American Indian tales about animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>



